
[1]thoughtful

   THOUGHT'FUL, a. Full of thought; contemplative; employed in meditation;
   as a man of thoughtful mind.

   1. Attentive; careful; having the mind directed to an object; as
   thoughtful of gain.

   2. Promoting serious thought; favorable to musing or meditation.

   War, horrid war, your thoughtful walks invades.

   3. Anxious; solicitous.

   Around her crowd distrust and doubt and fear,

   And thoughtful foresight, and tormenting care.
     __________________________________________________________________

